# data-testid conventions

Use **`data-testid`** (lowercase attribute name) on interactive elements and
key containers so Playwright/Cypress tests can target the UI reliably.

## Rules

1. **Kebab-case** values only (e.g. `add-client-field-first-name`).
2. **Prefix by feature/area**: `auth-`, `layout-`, `client-list-`,
   `add-client-`, `contact-field-`, `other-contact-field-`, `modal-`, etc.
3. **Centralize IDs** in `src/test-ids/index.js` — do not invent ad hoc
   strings in templates. Use helpers:
   - `addClientTestIds` (`tid`) — form, tabs, fields, buttons, accordions
   - `contactFieldTestId(name)`, `otherContactFieldTestId(name)`
   - `clientPageTestIds`, `clientListTestIds`, `layoutTestIds`, `authTestIds`
   - `modalTestIds` via `ModalComponent` `test-id` prop
4. **Shared components** accept `testId` / `test-id` and render
   `data-testid` on the underlying Quasar control (`TextInput`, `FormSelect`,
   `FormToggle`, `ClientDateField`, `AddClientLabeledField`,
   `AddClientMethodRowActions`, `AddClientAccordionSection`, `ModalComponent`).
5. **Row actions** include stable row identifiers when available
   (e.g. `clientListTestIds.rowEdit(row.id)`).
6. Avoid duplicate semantics: prefer one test id per logical control (field
   wrapper vs input may share the same id only when intentional).

## Adding new IDs

1. Add a constant or builder in `src/test-ids/index.js` using `toTestId` from
   `src/utils/test-id.js`.
2. Wire the template via the matching helper or component prop.
3. Run `npm run lint` after changes under `src/`.

## Examples

```vue
<FormSelect
  v-model="form[ck.race]"
  :test-id="tid.field(ck.race)"
/>
<q-btn :data-testid="tid.btn('next')" />
<ModalComponent test-id="cancel-discard" />
```

Login page:

```vue
<TextInput :test-id="authTestIds.emailInput" />
<q-btn :data-testid="authTestIds.signInButton" />
```
